      "name": "\u200b\u200bSupply Chain Compromise Impacts Axios Node Package Manager\u200b",
      "description": "On March 31, 2026, two npm packages for versions axios@1.14.1 and axios@0.30.4 of Axios npm injected the malicious dependency plain-crypto-js@4.2.1 that downloads multi-stage payloads from cyber threat actor infrastructure, including a remote access trojan. In addition, CISA recommends organizations using Axios npm: Mandate phishing-resistant multifactor authentication (MFA) on all developer accounts, especially for critical platforms.",
